441
00:23:33,800 --> 00:23:37,560
a doctor or scientist, like severely
Midwestern Diane Keaton here,

442
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:39,280
making an outlandish claim.

443
00:23:39,480 --> 00:23:40,960
But, it's worth checking

444
00:23:41,040 --> 00:23:44,080
if most credible doctors
or scientists agree with them.

445
00:23:44,160 --> 00:23:45,240
If you're thinking:

446
00:23:45,320 --> 00:23:47,840
"What if all of them are in
on the cover-up, too?"

447
00:23:47,920 --> 00:23:50,600
That actually brings us
to our final question here:

448
00:23:50,680 --> 00:23:54,360
"How plausible is this conspiracy,
as a practical matter?"

449
00:23:54,440 --> 00:23:57,240
Because not every conspiracy theory
is fictional.

450
00:23:57,320 --> 00:24:00,560
Obviously, some have absolutely
turned out to be true.

451
00:24:00,640 --> 00:24:02,920
But the very fact that we know
about the real ones

452
